&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About GLC Advisors &amp;amp; Co., LLC&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;GLC Advisors &amp;amp; Co., LLC (GLC) is a leading independent investment banking advisory firm delivering objective, senior-level expertise to execute financial advisory assignments for its clients. GLC has been ranked in the top 10 in Thomson Reuters’ US Restructuring Advisors from 2010-2025. Recently, GLC has been involved in many high-profile restructurings, including Hertz, Puerto Rico, Toys “R” Us, iHeartMedia, FirstEnergy, and Caesars Entertainment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The senior professionals at GLC have advised on over 850 transactions involving more than $820 billion of debt, equity linked and equity securities. The senior team at GLC has worked together over the past decade and brings financial advisory experience from AlixPartners, Credit Suisse First Boston, Donaldson, Lufkin &amp;amp; Jenrette, Morgan Stanley, PriceWaterhouseCoopers, Smith Barney, and UBS. GLC offers comprehensive services to its clients across many industries including: restructuring &amp;amp; recapitalization, financing &amp;amp; debt advisory, mergers &amp;amp; acquisitions, and valuation &amp;amp; fairness opinions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Offering&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Our New York office is seeking to recruit talented individuals to join the 2026 Full-Time Analyst class (starting summer 2026) for our growing restructuring practice. Analysts provide direct support to senior bankers and are expected to handle a high level of responsibility in the execution of restructuring and distressed financing transactions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing companies, industries, historical financial statements and prospective financial information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building financial models and performing valuation analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting industry and company research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and executing due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing presentations and other materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional work ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undergraduate degree from an outstanding institution with exceptional academic achievement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working as an Analyst within a bulge-bracket, major or boutique investment bank is preferred (prior experience in restructuring, leveraged finance or debt capital markets is ideal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Also open to accounting majors who wish to transition to investment banking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong modeling and financial statement analysis skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
